      <description>The U.S.-led coalition must provide both symbolic acknowledgment of civilians killed by their airstrikes in Syria and material assistance to the victims’ surviving loved ones, according to Nadim Houry, the director of Human Rights Watch’s program on terrorism and counterterrorism.</description>
